The paper deals with dynamic problems and their hardness, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. The use of matrix-vector multiplication and its conjecture implies connections to computational complexity (cs.CC) and combinatorial geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the use of polynomial hardness results, which suggests connections to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
